# Desktop portable + installer (always rebuild together)

The **only** bundled app tree is `desktop\app\`. It is rebuilt from root sources — never edit `desktop\app\` by hand.

## On every code change

`commit.bat` **always** (by default):

1. Syncs `backend/`, `frontend/dist`, `launcher/` → `desktop/app/`
2. Runs `npm run dist` → rebuilds **portable + installer + share folder**
3. Commits and pushes

You do **not** need a separate `dist` argument. Every edit that ends in `commit.bat` updates both builds.

| Output | Path |
|--------|------|
| Portable | `desktop\release\win-unpacked\QS Assistant.exe` |
| Installer | `desktop\release\QS-Assistant-Setup.exe` |
| Share zip source | `dist\QS-Assistant-Share\` |

## Manual commands

| Command | When |
|---------|------|
| `npm run desktop:sync` | Sync only, no electron build (rare) |
| `npm run dist` | Rebuild portable + installer without committing |
| `npm run share` | Refresh share folder from existing release |
| `commit.bat "msg" skip-dist` | Commit without rebuilding (docs-only / broken lock) |

## Do not use stale paths

- Do **not** rely on committed files under `desktop\app\` (gitignored).
- Do **not** hand-edit `desktop\release\` — it is overwritten each `commit.bat`.
- Legacy Inno `installer\QS-Assistant.iss` is optional; primary path is electron-builder.

## Source of truth

| Source | Copied to |
|--------|-----------|
| `backend\` | `desktop\app\backend\` |
| `frontend\dist\` | `desktop\app\backend\frontend-dist\` |
| `launcher\*.ps1` | `desktop\app\launcher\` |
